\v 13 People who live in nations near us make fun of us;
\q2 they laugh at us and deride/belittle us.
\q1
\v 14 They make jokes using the name of \add our country\add*,
\q2 they shake their heads \add to indicate that they despise us\add*.
\q1
\v 15 All day I feel disgraced;
\q2 from seeing my face, people know that I am ashamed.
\q1
\v 16 I hear what those who sneer at me and revile me say;
\q2 I am ashamed in front of my enemies and those who want to harm me.
\b
\q1
\v 17 All these things have happened to us
\q2 even though we have not forgotten you,
\q2 and we are not the ones who disobeyed the agreement you made with\add our ancestors\add*.
\q1
\v 18 We have not stopped being loyal to you,
\q2 and we have not stopped doing what you want us to do [IDI].
\q1
\v 19 But \add it is as though\add* you have allowed us to be helpless among wild animals,
\q2 and abandoned us in a deep dark \add ravine\add*.
